title: Katie Price shaken after being caught up in Westminster shooting
text:
GETTY TRAUMATIC: Katie was at Westminster when the attack occurred 
It is believed that 12 people have been injured in an incident in Westminster after a man brandishing a knife was shot by police. 
The Loose Women star concerned fans when she took to Twitter to ask: "Does anyone know what's happened on Westminster bridge hell of a lot of police cars ambulance traffic." 
Upon realising what was going on, the 38-year-old tweeted: "Omg I was right by Westminster when it just happened, like a scene from a film." 
The mum-of-five was not harmed in the incident. 
AFP HORROR: 12 people were injured in the incident Live images: Terror attack outside Parliament Wednesday, 22nd March 2017 Two people shot outside Parliament as car mows down 10 people in Westminster 1 / 19 EPA Armed police push people back following major incidents outside the Houses of Parliament in central London “Omg I was right by Westminster when it just happened” Katie Price 
Fans rushed to check if Katie was alright following her worrying tweets. 
However, many were angry with her for tweeting about being near the tragedy. 
One person replied: "That seems a little crass", with another adding: "It's not all about you Katie FFS." Related articles
